        "content": "<p>The Master Series uses <strong>10Cr15CoMoV steel</strong>, Xinzuo’s refined take on VG10-class performance. See how this steel compares in testing. <a href=\"/blogs/news/vg10-steel-vs-10cr15comov-guide\">VG10 vs 10Cr15CoMoV compared</a></p><p>Learn how <strong>67-layer Damascus</strong> cladding protects the cutting core while creating the Master Series’ signature wave pattern. <a href=\"/blogs/news/damascus-pattern-performance-price-guide\">Damascus pattern guide</a></p><p>Understand what <strong>steel hardness</strong> at 60 HRC means for edge retention, toughness, and ease of maintenance. <a href=\"/blogs/news/knife-steel-hardness-guide\">Steel hardness guide</a></p><p>Proper care keeps your Damascus blades performing and looking their best for years. <a href=\"/blogs/news/how-to-care-for-damascus-steel-knives\">Damascus knife care guide</a></p><p>Compare all Xinzuo and Hezhen knife series side by side — steel, hardness, handles, and pricing. <a href=\"/blogs/news/xinzuo-knives-series-comparison-guide\">Full series comparison guide</a></p><p>Looking for an ultra-premium upgrade? The <strong>Elegant Series</strong> pairs the same 10Cr steel with refined aesthetics. <a href=\"/collections/b38l-elegant-series\">Shop the Elegant Series</a></p>",
